TruckNav Pro Privacy Policy - Plain Language Version
Last Updated: January 2025
The Short Version
We collect your info to make the app work. We don't sell your data. Ever.
What We Collect
Stuff you give us:
Your email, name, and password when you sign up
Your truck details (size, weight, hazmat, etc.)
Routes and trips you create
Your driving hours (HOS logs)
Expenses and receipt photos you upload
Stuff we collect automatically:
Your location (for navigation)
What device you're using
How you use the app
Crash reports (to fix bugs)
From other companies:
Maps from Google
Login info if you use "Sign in with Apple"
Apple handles all payments - we never see your credit card
What We Do With Your Data
Give you truck-safe GPS directions
Track your Hours of Service
Help you track expenses for taxes
Calculate mileage deductions
Sync your stuff across devices
Fix problems and improve the app
Send you important app updates (not ads)
Where Your Data Lives
Cloud: Encrypted database (Supabase)
Your phone: Cached maps and offline data
Apple Keychain: Your login credentials (secure)
Everything is encrypted. We use the same security banks use.
Who Sees Your Data
We NEVER sell your data. We only share with:
Google Maps - for maps and directions
Supabase - stores your data securely
RevenueCat - handles subscriptions
Apple - processes payments
These companies can only use your data to provide their services to us. We might share data if:
The law requires it (court order, etc.)
DOT/FMCSA needs your HOS logs for an audit
How Long We Keep Things
Your account data: As long as you have an account
After you delete your account: Gone within 30 days
HOS logs: 6 months (required by law)
Expense records: 7 years (IRS recommendation)
Your Choices
You can:
Edit your profile and settings anytime in the app
Export your trips, HOS logs, and expenses
Delete your entire account (Settings → Account → Delete Account)
Turn off location access in your phone settings
Turn off notifications
California residents: You have extra rights under CCPA. Email privacy@trucknavpro.com. European residents: You have extra rights under GDPR. Same email.
About Location Tracking
Why we need it:
Turn-by-turn directions
Finding truck-safe routes (avoiding low bridges, weight limits)
Traffic updates
Automatic HOS logging
Mileage tracking for taxes
You control it: Change location permissions anytime in iOS Settings.
Kids
This app is for adults only. You need a CDL to drive a commercial truck (minimum age 18-21). We don't collect data from anyone under 18.
Changes to This Policy
If we change something important, we'll let you know in the app and ask for your OK.
Questions?
Privacy questions: privacy@trucknavpro.com
General support: support@trucknavpro.com
By using TruckNav Pro, you agree to this policy. © 2025 TruckNav Pro
